CSI API ETABS v1

cAnalysisResults Methods

The cAnalysisResults type exposes the following members.

Methods
NameDescription
AreaForceShell
Reports the area forces for the specified area elements that are assigned shell section properties (not plane or asolid properties). Note that the forces reported are per unit of in-plane length.
AreaJointForceShell
Reports the area joint forces for the point elements at each corner of the specified area elements that have shell-type properties
AreaStrainShell
AreaStrainShellLayered
AreaStressShell
Reports the area stresses for the specified area elements that are assigned shell section properties. Stresses are reported at each point element associated with the area element
AreaStressShellLayered
Reports the area stresses for the specified area elements that are assigned layered shell section properties
AssembledJointMass
Reports the assembled joint masses for the specified point elements
AssembledJointMass_1
Reports the assembled joint masses for the specified point elements
BaseReact
Reports the structure total base reactions
BaseReactWithCentroid
Reports the structure total base reactions and includes information on the centroid of the translational reaction forces
BucklingFactor
Reports buckling factors obtained from buckling load cases
FrameForce
Reports the frame forces for the specified line elements
FrameJointForce
Reports the frame joint forces for the point elements at each end of the specified line elements
GeneralizedDispl
Reports the displacement values for the specified generalized displacements
JointAcc
Reports the joint accelerations for the specified point elements. The accelerations reported by this function are relative accelerations.
JointAccAbs
Reports the joint absolute accelerations for the specified point elements. Absolute and relative accelerations are the same, except when reported for time history load cases subjected to acceleration loading
JointDispl
Reports the joint displacements for the specified point elements. The displacements reported by this function are relative displacements
JointDisplAbs
Reports the absolute joint displacements for the specified point elements. Absolute and relative displacements are the same except when reported for time history load cases subjected to acceleration loading
JointDrifts
Reports the joint drifts
JointReact
Reports the joint reactions for the specified point elements. The reactions reported are from restraints, springs and grounded (one-joint) links.
JointVel
Reports the joint velocities for the specified point elements. The velocities reported by this function are relative velocities
JointVelAbs
Reports the joint absolute velocities for the specified point elements. Absolute and relative velocities are the same, except when reported for time history load cases subjected to acceleration loading
LinkDeformation
Reports the link internal deformations
LinkForce
Reports the link forces at the point elements at the ends of the specified link elements
LinkJointForce
Reports the joint forces at the point elements at the ends of the specified link elements
ModalLoadParticipationRatios
Reports the modal load participation ratios for each selected modal analysis case
ModalParticipatingMassRatios
Reports the modal participating mass ratios for each mode of each selected modal analysis case
ModalParticipationFactors
Reports the modal participation factors for each mode of each selected modal analysis case
ModalPeriod
Reports the modal period, cyclic frequency, circular frequency and eigenvalue for each selected modal load case
ModeShape
Reports the modal displacements (mode shapes) for the specified point elements
PanelZoneDeformation
Reports the panel zone (link) internal deformations
PanelZoneForce
Reports the panel zone (link) forces at the point elements at the ends of the specified panel zone (link) elements
PierForce
Retrieves pier forces for any defined pier objects in the model
SectionCutAnalysis
Reports the section cut force for sections cuts that are specified to have an Analysis (F1, F2, F3, M1, M2, M3) result type
SectionCutDesign
Reports the section cut force for sections cuts that are specified to have a Design (P, V2, V3, T, M2, M3) result type
SpandrelForce
Retrieves spandrel forces for any defined spandrel objects in the model
StoryDrifts
Reports the story drifts
